HEADWORD: Framing
<hw>Fram"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act, process, or
style of putting together a frame, or of constructing anything; a frame;
that which frames.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch. & Engin.)</fld> <def>A framework, or a sy<?/
of frames.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Framing chisel</b></col> <fld>(Carp.)</fld>, <cd>a heavy
chisel with a socket shank for making mortises.</cd></cs></p>

